name: Chet Baker in 1953
description:
This is an old work of mine created in 2019, adapting the photographic work of a Bob Willoughby as a study of drawing portraits using Chinese ink.
I am an admirer of Chet Baker from his side as a jazz musician and him as an artist who has a unique character.
Therefore, on this occasion, I dedicate this work to the late Chet Baker as a symbol of admiration.

Basic work using Chinese ink on paper.
